File: A rugby ball seen on the field. Pixabay/hirobi JOHANNESBURG - Sanzaar has announced that the Springboks will still be playing in the Rugby Championship until at least 2025. SA Rugby,  Australia, New Zealand and Argentina have all secured their spot in the competition, with 2025 being the end of the current broadcasting cycle. For some time now, there have been murmurs of South Africa possibly moving to the Six Nations, and this could still happen but only after 2025. READ: Queensland to host rest of Rugby Championships: Sanzaar SARU has informed Sanzaar it will be exploring its options in future. This year, the competition will be played in full and all four countries will host matches. Siya Kolisi and company have two Tests against the All Blacks in August before a date with Argentina in Durban in September.